        void onReadOriginProgressDetail(int day,
                                java.lang.String date,
                                int allPackage,
                                int currentPackage)
        Returns the details of the reading. The location of this package needs to be remembered. The next time you read the data, the location of this package is passed in to avoid repeated reading
        parameters:
        day - data flag in the watch[0=Today,1=Yesterday,2=the day before yesterday]
        date - Date of data,format isyyyy-mm-dd
        allPackage - Total number of packets for the day
        currentPackage - location of this bag
